The fetch call closes the :from slot. The HTTP request, parse, and template fill all happen as one atomic speech shot. No local cache, no stale intermediate—just wire to utterance.

[VISUAL: A wire from the internet endpoint flowing directly into the `{condition}` hole inside the speech bubble, all enclosed by a single paren.]

