## Nested Wire-Shots In Speech

Two wire calls: one fetches a user ID, the second fetches details using that ID. Both close a single speech act.

```scheme
(surface :say \"User {name} has {points} points.\"
         :from (fetch (string-append \"https://api.example/user/\"
                                     (cdr (assoc 'id (fetch \"https://api.example/session\"))))))
```

*[needs: fetch, string-append, surface :say :from integration]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire fetch to parse JSON; wire surface to walk nested keys -->

The inner fetch closes the URL construction. The outer fetch closes the :from. The :from closes the say. Two network calls, one speech shot.

