## Map The Many Into An Enumeration

You have a list of names. You want to say them all in one sentence: \"Your friends are Alice, Bob, and Carol.\"

```scheme
(surface :say \"Your friends are {friends}.\"
         :from (list (cons 'friends
                           (fold (lambda (name acc)
                                   (if (null? acc)
                                       name
                                       (string-append acc \", \" name)))
                                 \"\"
                                 '(\"Alice\" \"Bob\" \"Carol\")))))
```

*[needs: string-append]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire string-append to core runtime -->

The fold collapses the list into a comma-separated string. The fold closes the cons, the cons closes the list, the list closes the :from, the :from closes the say. One form speaks the many.

