## Conditional Slot Fill

If the user has a nickname, use it; otherwise use the formal name. Decide *inside* the data record construction.

```scheme
(let ((profile (cortex/recall :topic \"user-profile\")))
  (surface :say \"Hello, {name}!\"
           :from (list (cons 'name 
                             (if (assoc 'nickname profile)
                                 (cdr (assoc 'nickname profile))
                                 (cdr (assoc 'formal-name profile)))))))
```

The if-expression closes the cons. The decision about which name to use happens in place, in the same form that builds the data and speaks it.

---

## Speech From A Calculation

The data isn't stored—it's computed on the fly. Count something, speak the count.

```scheme
(surface :say \"You have {count} unread messages.\"
         :from (list (cons 'count 
                           (length (cortex/recall :topic \"messages/unread\")))))
```

The length call closes the cons. The cons closes the list. The list closes the :from. The calculation *is* the retrieval.

