## Time-Dependent Template Selection

If it's morning, say \"Good morning.\" Otherwise, say \"Hello.\" The clock call and the decision both close the speech form.

```scheme
(let ((hour (cdr (assoc 'hour (clock/now)))))
  (surface :say (if (< hour 12)
                    \"Good morning, {name}!\"
                    \"Hello, {name}!\")
           :from (cortex/recall :topic \"user-name\")))
```

The clock call closes the hour binding. The comparison closes the if. The if closes the template. The recall closes the :from. Time-aware speech in one form.

