## Speech With Inline Calculation And Guard

Calculate a percentage. If it's above a threshold, say one thing; otherwise say another.

```scheme
(let ((total (cdr (assoc 'total (cortex/recall :topic \"progress\"))))
      (done (cdr (assoc 'done (cortex/recall :topic \"progress\")))))
  (let ((pct (* 100 (/ done total))))
    (surface :say (if (> pct 75)
                      \"You're almost done: {pct}% complete!\"
                      \"Keep going: {pct}% complete.\")
             :from (list (cons 'pct (inexact->exact (round pct)))))))
```

*[needs: inexact->exact, round]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire inexact->exact and round to core runtime -->

Two recalls, a calculation, a guard, a speech act—one nested let-form. The math closes the :from, the :from closes the say.

