## Registry + Recall In One Speech Act

Check a system capability, check a user preference, speak both.

```scheme
(surface :say \"Your device {support} feature X, and you have it {enabled}.\"
         :from (list (cons 'support 
                           (if (system/registry :domain \"features\" :key \"X\")
                               \"supports\"
                               \"does not support\"))
                     (cons 'enabled
                           (if (cdr (assoc 'feature-X-enabled 
                                           (cortex/recall :topic \"preferences\")))
                               \"enabled\"
                               \"disabled\"))))
```

Two retrieval systems—registry and cortex—one data construction, one utterance. The if-expressions decide the wording in place.

