## Speech With Honest Escalation

If the data is missing, escalate instead of speaking nonsense.

```scheme
(let ((profile (cortex/recall :topic \"user-profile\")))
  (if (eq? profile 'nan)
      (escalate \"Cannot greet user: profile not found\")
      (surface :say \"Hello, {name}!\" :from profile)))
```

*[needs: escalate]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire escalate verb -->

One let, one guard, two branches: escalate or speak. The whole decision is one form. No silent failure, no half-filled template.

