## Conditional Wire-Shot In Speech

Fetch from endpoint A if a flag is true, otherwise from endpoint B.

```scheme
(let ((use-primary (cdr (assoc 'use-primary (cortex/recall :topic \"config\")))))
  (surface :say \"Data: {value}\"
           :from (fetch (if use-primary
                            \"https://api.example/primary\"
                            \"https://api.example/fallback\"))))
```

*[needs: fetch]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire fetch -->

The if-expression closes the URL. The fetch closes the :from. The recall closes the let. One form decides which wire to pull and speaks the result.

