## Speech With Computed Plurality

If the count is 1, say \"message\". Otherwise, say \"messages\". Compute and inflect in place.

```scheme
(let ((count (length (cortex/recall :topic \"messages/unread\"))))
  (surface :say (if (= count 1)
                    \"You have 1 message.\"
                    \"You have {count} messages.\")
           :from (list (cons 'count count))))
```

The if-expression chooses the template based on the count. The count closes the cons, the cons closes the :from, the :from closes the say. Grammar and data in one shot.

