## Guarded Multi-Source Speech With Defaults

Three recalls. If any returns `'nan`, substitute a default. Speak all three.

```scheme
(surface :say \"{name} from {city}, score: {score}.\"
         :from (let ((name-rec (cortex/recall :topic \"user-name\"))
                     (city-rec (cortex/recall :topic \"user-city\"))
                     (score-rec (cortex/recall :topic \"user-score\")))
                 (list (cons 'name (if (eq? name-rec 'nan) 
                                       \"Unknown\" 
                                       (cdr (assoc 'name name-rec))))
                       (cons 'city (if (eq? city-rec 'nan) 
                                       \"Unknown\" 
                                       (cdr (assoc 'city city-rec))))
                       (cons 'score (if (eq? score-rec 'nan) 
                                        0 
                                        (cdr (assoc 'score score-rec)))))))
```

Three recalls, three guards, three defaults—all in one let-form. Each if-expression closes a cons. The list of conses closes the :from. The :from closes the say. Honest nulls, honest defaults, one shot.

