## Speech With Time Window Guard

If it's between 9 AM and 5 PM, say one thing. Otherwise, say another.

```scheme
(let ((hour (cdr (assoc 'hour (clock/now)))))
  (surface :say (if (and (>= hour 9) (< hour 17))
                    \"The office is open. Call {number}.\"
                    \"The office is closed. Try again during business hours.\")
           :from (cortex/recall :topic \"contact-info\")))
```

The clock call closes the hour binding. The comparison closes the if. The if closes the template. The recall closes the :from. Time-gated speech in one form.

