## Speech With Guard And Multi-Branch Case

If the data is missing, escalate. If it's present, pick a template based on a field value.

```scheme
(let ((record (cortex/recall :topic \"status\")))
  (if (eq? record 'nan)
      (escalate \"Status data unavailable\")
      (let ((level (cdr (assoc 'level record))))
        (surface :say (case level
                        ((low) \"Status is low: {message}\")
                        ((medium) \"Status is medium: {message}\")
                        ((high) \"Status is high: {message}\"))
                 :from record))))
```

*[needs: escalate]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire escalate -->

One recall, one guard, one case, one speech act. The case closes the template. The record closes the :from. The :from closes the say. Guard and polymorphism in one form.

